entries.title: Bolsonaro Supporters Storm Brazil's Congress Buildings
entries.description: Thousands of protesters stormed Congress buildings in the capital Brasília Sunday, many calling for military intervention to remove leftist leader Luiz Inácio Lula da Silva.

entries.title: Sweden Can't Meet Turkey's Demands on NATO Expansion, Prime Minister Says
entries.description: Turkey’s extradition requests must be handled in accordance with the country’s laws, says Ulf Kristersson.

entries.title: Egyptians Cut Back on Staples as Inflation Rises
entries.description: Egypt has been hit especially hard after the war in Ukraine pushed up global commodities prices and the local currency weakened.

entries.title: Russia's Cease-Fire in Ukraine Ends With Few Signs Fighting Abated
entries.description: Russian forces continued shelling across eastern Ukraine and Moscow-installed officials accused Ukrainian forces of bombing a power plant in occupied Donetsk.

entries.title: Biden Heads to Southern Border Facing Criticism From Both Parties
entries.description: Democrats are decrying his use of Trump-era policies, while Republicans say he hasn’t done enough to stem illegal crossings.

entries.title: Germany Detains Iranian Suspected of Planning Chemical Attack
entries.description: Police raided the 32-year-old man’s apartment, who was suspected of obtaining cyanide and ricin to allegedly plan a “serious act of violence.”

entries.title: China Reopens to the World
entries.description: Thousands of international travelers arrived at and flew out of mainland Chinese airports as Beijing removed almost all of its Covid-era border restrictions after three years.
